description:
Institute for Analytical Chemistry. University of Vienna, W&auml;hringerstrasse 38, A-1090 Vienna, Austria 

 A method for the isolation of nickel from mineral waters by solvent extraction and cation exchange is described. The nickel is first preconcentrated from the waters by chloroform extraction in its dimethylgIyoximate form at  \(p\) H 7.4-7.6. The chloro&shy;form extract is then mixed with THF and methanol containing hydrochloric acid, and passed through a column of Dowex 50-X8 (H +  form) :  After removal of dimethylgly&shy; oxime, chloroform and THF by washing the resin with methanol-HCI, nickel is elated with 6 M  HCI and determined by a.a.s. with an air-acetyleneThe method was successfully applied to determine nickel in bottled mineral waters in which nickel in the range from 0.3 to 30  &micro; g Ni/litre was found. 

